---
source: tests/cli_help.rs
expression: stdout
---
mind-forge: a local-first knowledge management CLI

Usage: mf [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  init        Initialize a directory as a Mind Repo
  project     Manage projects
  article     Manage articles
  source      Manage content sources
  asset       Manage project assets
  term        Manage terminology [aliases: terms]
  prompt      Inspect article writing-prompt bindings
  thinking    Inspect article thinking-ledger bindings
  build       Build articles
  publish     Publish articles to configured targets
  render      Generate render prompts (emits prompts only, no output files)
  config      Manage configuration
  completion  Generate shell completion scripts
  version     Show version information

Options:
      --root <PATH>      Mind Repo root directory
      --config <PATH>    Config file path
  -v, --verbose...       Verbose output
  -q, --quiet            Silence non-error output
  -o, --output <FORMAT>  Output format [default: text] [possible values: text, json]
      --json             Shorthand for --output json
      --no-color         Disable colored output
  -p, --project <NAME>   Project name for project-scoped operations
  -h, --help             Print help
  -V, --version          Print version
